{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_vrtx_01AU7UMPx6mVZSfeBLUky7s2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I now have complete context. Here is the full implementation:\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\nThe implementation mirrors the trustmanager pattern by:\n1. Adding a `computeCABundleHash` function (SHA-256 of PEM data)\n2. Threading the hash through the volume update chain so it gets stamped as a pod template annotation\n3. Extending `deploymentSpecModified` to compare pod template annotations (idempotency guard)\n\n---\n\n## File 1: NEW — `pkg/controller/istiocsr/configmaps.go`\n\n```go\npackage istiocsr\n\nimport (\n\t\"crypto/sha256\"\n\t\"encoding/hex\"\n)\n\n// computeCABundleHash returns the SHA-256 hash of the CA bundle PEM content.\n// The hash is used as the pod template annotation to trigger rolling restarts\n// only when the actual certificate content changes.\nfunc computeCABundleHash(caBundle string) string {\n\thash := sha256.Sum256([]byte(caBundle))\n\treturn hex.EncodeToString(hash[:])\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## File 2: NEW — `pkg/controller/istiocsr/configmaps_test.go`\n\n```go\npackage istiocsr\n\nimport (\n\t\"testing\"\n)\n\nfunc TestComputeCABundleHash(t *testing.T) {\n\ttests := []struct {\n\t\tname     string\n\t\tbundle1  string\n\t\tbundle2  string\n\t\twantSame bool\n\t}{\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname:     \"same bundle produces same hash\",\n\t\t\tbundle1:  \"-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----\\ntest\\n-----END CERTIFICATE-----\",\n\t\t\tbundle2:  \"-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----\\ntest\\n-----END CERTIFICATE-----\",\n\t\t\twantSame: true,\n\t\t},\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname:     \"different bundles produce different hashes\",\n\t\t\tbundle1:  \"-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----\\ntest1\\n-----END CERTIFICATE-----\",\n\t\t\tbundle2:  \"-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----\\ntest2\\n-----END CERTIFICATE-----\",\n\t\t\twantSame: false,\n\t\t},\n\t}\n\n\tfor _, tt := range tests {\n\t\tt.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n\t\t\thash1 := computeCABundleHash(tt.bundle1)\n\t\t\thash2 := computeCABundleHash(tt.bundle2)\n\n\t\t\tif hash1 == \"\" {\n\t\t\t\tt.Fatal(\"expected non-empty hash\")\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tif (hash1 == hash2) != tt.wantSame {\n\t\t\t\tt.Errorf(\"hash equality=%v, want %v (hash1=%s, hash2=%s)\", hash1 == hash2, tt.wantSame, hash1, hash2)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t})\n\t}\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## File 3: MODIFY — `pkg/controller/istiocsr/constants.go`\n\nAdd this constant inside the unnamed `const` block at line 83, after `IstiocsrCAKeyName` (line 89):\n\n```diff\n \t// IstiocsrCAKeyName is the key name holding the CA certificate in the issuer secret or the controller\n \t// CA configmap.\n \tIstiocsrCAKeyName = \"ca.crt\"\n+\n+\t// caConfigMapHashAnnotation is the pod template annotation that tracks the CA bundle hash.\n+\t// When the CA data changes, the hash changes, triggering a rolling restart.\n+\tcaConfigMapHashAnnotation = \"operator.openshift.io/ca-configmap-hash\"\n )\n```\n\nThe full constant block (lines 83–91) becomes:\n\n```go\n\t// IstiocsrCAConfigMapName is the name of the configmap which is mounted in istiocsr container, containing the\n\t// CA certificate configured in the secret referenced in the issuer.\n\tIstiocsrCAConfigMapName = istiocsrCommonName + \"-issuer-ca-copy\"\n\n\t// IstiocsrCAKeyName is the key name holding the CA certificate in the issuer secret or the controller\n\t// CA configmap.\n\tIstiocsrCAKeyName = \"ca.crt\"\n\n\t// caConfigMapHashAnnotation is the pod template annotation that tracks the CA bundle hash.\n\t// When the CA data changes, the hash changes, triggering a rolling restart.\n\tcaConfigMapHashAnnotation = \"operator.openshift.io/ca-configmap-hash\"\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n## File 4: MODIFY — `pkg/controller/istiocsr/deployments.go`\n\n### Change 1: `getDeploymentObject` — capture hash from `updateVolumes` and stamp it\n\nReplace lines 101–103:\n```go\n\tif err := r.updateVolumes(deployment, istiocsr, resourceLabels); err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, f