reateOrUpdateCAConfigMap`; stamp hash on pod template via `stampCABundleHash` |\n| `pkg/controller/istiocsr/utils.go` | **Modified** | Add `Spec.Template.Annotations` comparison in `deploymentSpecModified` for idempotency |\n\nThe flow mirrors trustmanager exactly: `createOrUpdateCAConfigMap` computes the hash, it bubbles up through `handleUserProvidedCA`/`handleIssuerBasedCA` → `updateVolumes` → `getDeploymentObject`, which stamps it as `operator.openshift.io/ca-configmap-hash` on the pod template. When the CA PEM data is unchanged, the hash matches the existing annotation, `deploymentSpecModified` returns false, and the update is skipped."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":19694,"cache_read_input_tokens":100203,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":19694,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"39bbe18b-fa63-412d-8593-1709be0f4036","uuid":"80422425-84ba-4a05-b17a-3d5e6a49b834","timestamp":"2026-07-20T13:53:49.688Z","request_id":"req_vrtx_011CdDRLSrJccHyQr6bfxDxR"}
